function maxEvents(events) {
    events.sort((a, b) => a[1] - b[1]);

    let count = 0;
    let lastDay = -1;

    for (const event of events) {
        if (event[0] > lastDay) {
            count++;
            lastDay = event[1];
        }
    }

    return count;
}
```

    The idea is to sort the events by end day. After sorting, iterate through the events and use a variable `lastDay` to keep track of the last day an event was attended. If the current event's start day is greater than the `lastDay`, increment the `count` (number of attended events) and set `lastDay` as the current event's end day. This greedy approach ensures we attend the events that end early and maximize the number of total attended events.

